              "rawHtml" : "<div style=\"background-color:#F3F3F3; padding-top:40px; padding-bottom:84px;\">\n  <p style=\"text-align:center;font-size:16px; font-family:Arial; line-height:24px; margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; \"><strong>Check out these tips</strong></p>\n  <hr style=\"color:#C9C9C9; margin-bottom:0px; margin-top:16px; margin-left:16px; margin-right:16px;\" />\n<div style=\"font-size:16px; font-family:Arial; line-height:24px; padding-top:32px;padding-left:16px; padding-right:16px;\">\n<p style=\"margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px;\">\n  When you&#39;re ready to change the look of your email, use the Email Style panel to set the background color and padding. Define the email layout to give your content a place to live. Click  <b>&#43; </b> on the canvas or drag an item from the Components panel to add and arrange the parts of your email. To add rows or columns, use the Section component.\n</p>\n<p style=\"margin-top:16px; margin-bottom:0px;\">  \nFor each component, you can change the padding, colors, and other properties in the Style panel. In the text components, like Paragraph and Heading, edit fonts, font size, and other formatting in the component itself. If you want to customize your message for each customer, add merge fields to a heading or paragraph by clicking <b>{}</b> in the component toolbar.\n</p>\n  </div>\n</div>"
